peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is an antique dresser with a mirror called?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: A dresser with a mirror on top is called a bureau. This type of storage furniture is essentially a cabinet with a stack of horizontal drawers. Typically, a bureau-dressing table is waist-high and placed in the bedroom. A bureau can also refer to a secretaire, a furnishing with a writing surface.
